// Testing the internal function `_splitAccount`.
AccountSplitterAndMerger_splitAccount
├── Given account is healthy
│   ├── Given valid fraction
│   │   ├── It should check account is healthy before splitting.
│   │   ├── It should create a new account with half the collateral shares.
│   │   ├── It should seed the new account with half the debt shares.
│   │   └── It should give the new account to the receiver.
│   └── Given invalid fraction
│       └── It should revert.
│           └── With `AccountSplitterAndMerger__InvalidFraction`.
├── Given account is unhealthy
│   └── It should revert.
│       └── With `Office__AccountNotHealthy`.
│           └── For the new account.
├── When caller is unauthorized
│   └── It should revert.
│       └── With `Office__UnauthorizedCaller`.
└── When callback function called directly
    └── It should revert.
        └── With `AccountSplitterAndMerger_onlyOffice`.
